				</textElement>
				<text><![CDATA[5.1.2. Selection of venous whole blood collection tube:  
<br>   ]]></text>
			</staticText>
		</band>
		<band height="135">
			<staticText>
				<reportElement positionType="Float" x="25" y="0" width="545" height="135" uuid="022eba2e-b80e-48ae-aaca-0a0175768a23"/>
				<textElement textAlignment="Justified" verticalAlignment="Middle" markup="html">
					<font size="12" pdfFontName="net/sf/jasperreports/fonts/dejavu/DejaVuSerif-Italic.ttf" isPdfEmbedded="true"/>
				</textElement>
				<text><![CDATA[In general, the blood ccfDNA can be influenced by inadequate blood collection procedures/storage/shipping conditions and ccfDNA isolation procedures. The post-collection release of genomic DNA from white blood cells can change the ccfDNA profile significantly. Using blood collection tubes containing ccfDNA profile stabilisers is therefore recommended. If no ccfDNA-stabilised tubes are used, EDTA blood collection tubes should be preferred over other collection tubes. Induced clotting processes in serum tubes can lead to leucocytes lysis and should therefore be avoided.]]></text>
			</staticText>
		</band>
